         <abstract>
            <p>
               The <foreign xml:lang="gez">Maṣḥafa krǝstǝnnā</foreign> is the service book for the administration of the Sacraments of Christian Initiation. It includes the preparatory rites and the threefold sercive
               of baptism, chrism and Eucharist. Its structure is the same as of the baptismal book of the Coptic Church.
            </p>
              <p>It is sometimes grouped in manuscripts with <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1975Mashaf">Maṣḥafa ṭǝmqat</ref>. 
            </p>
            <p>The long version agrees with the short versions <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3948MashafaKrS">Maṣḥafa krǝstǝnnā</ref> until the recitation of the Credo, then there are many added prayers. 
               The Psalms <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#Ps61"> 61</ref> and <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#Ps113">113, 20-end</ref> are absent.
               The <foreign xml:lang="gez">ṣawātǝw</foreign> prayers are more elaborated than in the short recension.</p>
         </abstract>
